    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1971-06-02T23:09:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1971-06-02T23:09:00-05:00" n="360"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                <head>360. Telegram From <gloss type="from">the Embassy in Japan</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d360fn1">Source: National Archives, RG 59,
                        Central Files 1970–73, <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> 6 <gloss
                            target="#t_CHIC1">CHICOM</gloss>. Secret; Exdis. Repeated to Hong Kong,
                        Paris, Taipei, and <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Tokyo</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1971-06-03T04:09:00+00:00">June 3, 1971, 0409Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5221. Subj: <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">Rogers</persName>–<persName
                        corresp="#p_AK1">Aichi</persName> talk re <gloss target="#t_CHIR1"
                        >Chirep</gloss> in Paris.<note n="2" xml:id="d360fn2">Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_RWP1">Rogers</persName> attended the OECD Ministerial
                        Council meeting in Paris June 6–9.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Summary: [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line of source text not
                    declassified</hi>] <gloss target="#t_PRIMIN1">PriMin</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SE1">Sato</persName> place highest importance on: a)
                    keeping <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss> in <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                    >UN</gloss>; and b) closest consultations with <gloss target="#t_USG1"
                        >USG</gloss> on China issues.</p>
                <pb facs="0741" n="704" xml:id="pg_704"/>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>During 90-minute session June 2, <gloss target="#t_PRIMIN1">PriMin</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SE1">Sato</persName> attached great hope to FornMin
                            <persName corresp="#p_AK1">Aichi</persName>’s forthcoming discussion re
                            <gloss target="#t_CHIR1">Chirep</gloss> with Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_RWP1">Rogers</persName> in Paris. [<hi rend="italic">4½
                            lines of source text not declassified</hi>]</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Stressing importance of continued close <gloss target="#t_USG1"
                            >USG</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss> consultations,
                            <persName corresp="#p_SE1">Sato</persName> observed that once course of
                        action is determined, <gloss target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss> can lobby
                        effectively with some countries, e.g. SEA nations, while <gloss
                            target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> can cultivate other territory, e.g. English
                        speaking world.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SE1">Sato</persName> said he has impression <gloss
                            target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> is still gathering info. He indicated
                        tempus is fugiting and much spadework will have to be done in anticipation
                        of <gloss target="#t_UNGA1">UNGA</gloss> this fall. He noted that because of
                        its involvement in Indo-China hostilities, in which <gloss target="#t_PRC1"
                            >PRC</gloss> has direct interest, situation is in some ways more
                        difficult for <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> than for <gloss
                            target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>According to <persName corresp="#p_SE1">Sato</persName>, of utmost
                        importance is close <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss>–<gloss
                            target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss> consultation. I noted we staying in close
                        touch but final <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> decision re course to be
                        followed not yet taken.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>When asked specifically what message he wished conveyed to Secretary,
                            <persName corresp="#p_SE1">Sato</persName> said it is <gloss
                            target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss>’s determination to honor its treaty
                        obligations with Taiwan, and to uphold its “international faith.” If <gloss
                            target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss> could keep its UNSC seat so much the
                        better, but in any case <gloss target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss> wishes to take
                        whatever steps may be necessary to assure that <gloss target="#t_GRC1"
                            >GRC</gloss> stays in <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>. He was glad to
                        have reassurance that <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> also wants <gloss
                            target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss>’s continuation in <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                            >UN</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SE1">Sato</persName> said Japan’s new chief <gloss
                            target="#t_REP1">rep</gloss> at <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NT2">Nakagawa</persName> has been instructed to sound
                        out U <persName corresp="#p_TU1">Thant</persName>’s views.</item>
                    <label>7.</label>
                    <item>Earlier in day, Vice FornMin <persName corresp="#p_MH2">Mori</persName>
                        had suggested to me that while it is <gloss target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss>’s
                        wish and <gloss target="#t_PRIMIN1">PriMin</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SE1">Sato</persName>’s strong determination to assure
                            <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss>’s preservation in <gloss
                            target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>, impression in <gloss target="#t_GOJ1"
                            >GOJ</gloss> circles is that <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss>’s
                        primary interest is maintaining bilateral commitment to <gloss
                            target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss>, with <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss>’s
                        status in <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> of lesser importance. I assured
                            <persName corresp="#p_MH2">Mori</persName> that we share <gloss
                            target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss>’s desire to keep <gloss target="#t_GRC1"
                            >GRC</gloss> in <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Meyer</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
